  "image_url": "https://cdn.kirtansewa.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/22005302/Bhai-Inderjit-Singh-ji-Derby.jpg",
  "body": [
    "Bhai Inderjeet Singh Ji is one of the last few students of Prof. Darshan Singh Ji Komal who is still continuing his legacy. He has been based in Derby, UK for decades but before that, he also visited Singapore and Malaysia in the 60s with his father-in-law, Bhai Sadhu Singh Ji from Hoshiarpur. Bhai Sadhu Singh Ji served as a Granthi in Singapore for 2 years and during that time Bhai Inderjeet Singh Ji accompanied him on tabla. To my knowledge, there were at least 2 spools of theirs which were recorded in Malaysia by Sardar Harcharan Singh Ji. Those spools went missing sometime in the 80s. If anyone has those spools or any other recordings of Bhai Sadhu Singh Ji and Bhai Inderjeet Singh Ji, please contact us."
